			"description" : "<p>In perhaps the most eventful year in decades for Bangor, 2013 saw the debut of the expanded and redesigned <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/05/06/living/2013-waterfront-concert-lineup/?ref=search'>Waterfront Concerts</a> in May and <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/slideshow/bangors-new-arena-wows-residents-near-and-far-during-open-house-event/?ref=search'>the opening of the Cross Insurance Center</a> in September. Though some in the community objected to <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/video/some-bangor-residents-concerned-about-noise-and-language-from-waterfront-concerts/?ref=search'>noise from the outdoor concerts</a>, several summer shows drew more than <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/slideshow/country-star-luke-bryan-plays-to-sold-out-waterfront-crowd/?ref=search'>16,000 people</a> to Bangor &mdash; spurring a strong season for local businesses. The Cross Center has attracted several midsize concerts, as well as a popular series of <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/07/27/living/broadway-shows-to-take-the-stage-at-cross-insurance-center/?ref=search'>touring Broadway shows</a>, the <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/11/13/living/maine-harvest-festival-to-be-held-at-cross-insurance-center/?ref=search'>Maine Harvest Festival </a>and <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/07/31/sports/umaine-sports/umaine-basketball-teams-to-play-most-games-at-cross-insurance-center/?ref=search'>University of Maine basketball games</a>. With staff at both venues promising more, bigger and better for 2014, could it be that the Queen City is becoming the Music City of Maine?</p>"
