			"description" : "<p>U.S. Rep. Mike Michaud, the Democratic candidate for the 2014 governor&rsquo;s race, <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/11/04/politics/elections/mike-michaud-announces-hes-gay-alleges-campaign-to-out-him-2/'>dominated headlines</a> in early November when <a href='https://bangordailynews.com/2013/11/04/opinion/mike-michaud-yes-i-am-gay-but-why-should-it-matter-2/'>he revealed that he is gay</a>. Michaud said he hadn&rsquo;t even told his mother, <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/11/27/politics/mike-michauds-mother-dies-at-79/'>who died late last month</a>, about his sexuality until the day of his announcement. Speculation abounded about the effect of the announcement on Michaud&rsquo;s campaign. Will his Catholic French-Canadian supporters, a key voting bloc, abandon him? Will his campaign find new financial support from national gay rights groups? Michaud deflected those questions and said, <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/11/04/politics/michaud-i-havent-changed-im-mike/'>&ldquo;I haven&rsquo;t changed. I&rsquo;m Mike.&rdquo;</a></p>"
