			"description" : "<p>The <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/05/23/news/bangor/bdn-stories-about-the-search-for-15-year-old-nichole-cable/?ref=relatedSidebar'>story of missing 15-year-old Nichole Cable</a> captured the <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/09/15/news/bangor/mother-stepfather-of-nichole-cable-to-appear-on-dr-phil-show/?ref=relatedBox'>attention of Mainers and the nation</a> after investigators revealed the Orono man accused of kidnapping and killing her &mdash; <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/06/06/news/bangor/new-affidavit-man-accused-of-killing-nichole-cable-tried-to-kiss-and-grope-her-in-previous-encounter/?ref=relatedBox'>rejected suitor</a> Kyle Dube &nbsp;&mdash; allegedly used text messages and a fake Facebook page to lure Cable from the safety of her Glenburn home on Mother&rsquo;s Day. The <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/05/23/news/bangor/bdn-stories-about-the-search-for-15-year-old-nichole-cable/?ref=relatedSidebar'>weeklong search</a> for the Old Town High School sophomore <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/05/20/news/bangor/items-found-authorities-pursuing-leads-in-search-for-glenburn-teen-nichole-cable/?ref=relatedSidebar'>unearthed physical</a> and electronic evidence linking her to Dube. Police found her body covered with sticks near a dam in Old Town and charged Dube, who <a href='http://bangordailynews.com/2013/05/29/news/bangor/death-of-15-year-old-nichole-cable-was-kidnapping-gone-wrong-affidavit-says/?ref=relatedBox'>claimed the crime was an abduction gone wrong</a>. His trial has not been scheduled.</p>"
